    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Mojave Desert</b> (322Ad, Af, Aj). Stands occur in Death Valley National Park in the Black, Funeral, and Owlshead Mountains, and in Mojave National Preserve near the Cinder Cone Lava Beds (Evens et al. 2014). However, stands are likely to occur further southwest in the region (e.g., 322An), and more sampling is needed to determine its full range.</li>
        
            <li><b>Southeastern Great Basin</b> (341Fc, Ff). Stands have been surveyed in Death Valley National Park in the Last Chance Range and Panamint Mountains (Evens et al. 2014).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
